        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(web): add publisher dashboard workspace",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nThis PR proposes an owner-aware publisher workspace for managing skills and plugins from one dashboard.\n\n- What changed: the signed-in dashboard gains publisher switching, actionable review states, catalog controls, download analytics, and direct publishing/import paths.\n- Why: publishers need one operational view for inventory, trust signals, performance, and publishing paths across personal and organization contexts.\n- Follow-up deferred: the platform changelog surface is intentionally removed for now.\n\n## What changed\n\n### Publisher context and navigation\n\n- Added personal and organization publisher switching with the active identity carried through dashboard queries and publishing links.\n- Added publisher-aware skill and plugin detail, settings, validation, and security-audit destinations.\n- Added authenticated loading, empty, timeout, and sign-in states for the dashboard.\n- Added a unified “Add skill or plugin” route with owner-aware defaults across dashboard and publishing entry points.\n- Removed the dashboard sidebar toggle icon beside “Add skill or plugin” so the header action row stays focused.\n\n### Package inventory\n\n- Rebuilt the package inventory around shared list and grid views for skills and plugins.\n- Added type filters, sorting, search disclosure, view switching, pagination, and URL-backed dashboard state.\n- Added persistent list/grid preferences.\n- Added package row menus with view, settings, audit, copy, and publishing actions appropriate to each artifact.\n- Added normalized catalog metadata, status labels, owner paths, canonical detail links, and download counts.\n\n### Trust and review workflow\n\n- Added a “Needs attention” surface that groups security, visibility, validation, and quality findings by artifact.\n- Added blocked, pending, and review severity states with concise context and hidden/removed visibility labels.\n- Added an in-dashboard SkillSpector review sheet with vulnerability patterns and findings.\n- Added an in-dashboard plugin validation sheet with CLI guidance, copyable instructions, error/warning groups, and remediation details.\n- Routed plugin security reviews to the canonical audit surface and retained validation-specific destinations where appropriate.\n- Added manager-scoped plugin inspector findings and the package metadata needed to render real review states.\n\n### Download analytics\n\n- Added publisher-scoped download metrics for skills, plugins, and combined inventory.\n- Added 1-day, 1-week, 1-month, and all-time views with daily series, comparison deltas, chart labels, and tooltips.\n- Added per-item metric selection for skills and plugins.\n- Included complete publisher inventories and legacy personal ownership in aggregate and selected-item metrics.\n- Read canonical skill stats and real package daily stats instead of synthetic chart data.\n\n### Dashboard sidebar and changelog removal\n\n- Kept the dashboard sidebar focused on GitHub import.\n- Removed the proposed `/changelog` route, platform changelog data, changelog sidebar feed, and related styles/tests for now.\n- Removed stale changelog screenshots from this PR body so the proposal does not advertise a postponed surface.\n\n### Shared UI and coverage\n\n- Extended shared browse controls, header behavior, select rendering, skeletons, route generation, and responsive dashboard styles.\n- Added focused coverage for dashboard routing, catalog behavior, attention states, and download metrics.\n- Updated generated Convex API types for the new dashboard query surface.\n\n## Linked Issue\n\n- Closes N/A\n- Related N/A\n\n## Behavioural Proof\n\nVerified the dashboard change locally after rebasing onto `upstream/main`. The focused dashboard test now asserts the proposed header no longer renders the sidebar toggle and the proposed sidebar no longer renders “Latest updates”.\n\n- [x] Behavioural proof included\n\n## Security / Trust Impact\n\nThis PR adds authenticated publisher-scoped reads and manager-scoped inspector findings to render existing security, visibility, and validation state. It reuses the existing identity, publisher membership, ownership, and audit route boundaries; it does not add moderation or scanner write actions.\n\n- [ ] No security/trust impact\n- [x] Security/trust impact explained\n\n## Data / Deploy Impact\n\nNo schema migration or backfill is required. The change adds Convex query code and generated API typing, so the backend and web app must be deployed together.\n\n- [ ] No data/deploy impact\n- [x] Data/deploy impact explained\n\n## Verification\n\n- [x] `bun run test -- src/routes/-dashboard.test.tsx`\n- [x] `bun run ci:static`\n- [x] `bun run ci:unit`\n- [x] `bun run ci:types-build`\n- [x] `git diff --check upstream/main...HEAD`\n",
        "branch": "brzezowski/publisher-dashboard-workspace",
